result.execSummary:
The defendant Yadiel Nunez-Munoz was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Aggravated Battery-Intend GreatBod. Harm [Modifiers: Use of a Dangerous Weapon], a class E felony, Wisconsin Statutes 940.19(5).
  • Attempt 1st-Degree Intentional Homicide [Modifiers: Use Dangerous Weapon (Felony 5+ Yrs)], a class B felony, Wisconsin Statutes 940.01(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Concur to ct 2 but consec to Florida sentence.  Defendant is eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program.  Defendant is eligible for the Substance Abuse Program.

superMiscConds.notes: DA has 90 days to prepare/submit order.

$250 DNA surcharge remitted. $268  to be collected by the Dept of Corrections.  Court financial obligations shall be paid at the rate of 25% of the prison wages and work release funds.  Restitution shall be paid pursuant to separate court order.
Any other conditions DOC, Probation/Parole Department may impose.

Court explains that we will be doing instructions, we will have an early lunch, and then come back hear closing and then go out for deliberations. Gonzalez argues the instructions are wrong. ADA Jambois agrees that the wording should be changed.
Court has jury instructions retrieved and will be corrected. All photographs can go, bank records, 911 transcript. Gun not allowed. Exhibit 58-counsel will be notified if requested. Court has read the verdict.  Count 1, GUILTY. Count 2, GUILTY. Court polls jurors, all answers are yes. Jurors are excused at 9:50. State moves for judgment of verdict.  Bail revoked.
